HEADWORD: Mandibuliform
<hw>Man`di*bu"li*form</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Having the form of a mandible; -- said
especially of the maxillae of an insect when hard and adapted for
biting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mandibulohyoid</ent>⟦br⟧
